            usually building web applications in <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/" rel="nofollow">Rails</a>, simple tools in <a href="http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/" rel="nofollow">Ruby</a>
            and sometimes in PHP (from which I try to escape). Besides that I like to get better at Python, Java, Haskell and Erlang as well as designing with JavaScript, HTML and SCSS.
            I&nbsp;try to write serious things on my <a href="http://blog.oldrichvetesnik.cz/">blog</a> and nonsense on <a href="http://www.mrmil.cz/">Mrmil.cz</a> (although I don't write much).

